cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.SE 

The paper deals with detecting malicious activities in compromised machines, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of algorithms such as Spearman's rank correlation and Dendritic Cell Algorithm suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The detection of keylogging and packet flooding behaviour involves network intrusion detection (cs.NI) and the analysis of system behaviour (cs.SE).
